          },
          "displayName": "Steve Loughran",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Europe/London"
        },
        "body": "I'm going to submit an initial patch soon, but want to flag up something first. Should CompositeService attempt to {{stop()}} all its child services when told to {{stop()}} itself - regardless of what state the it is in? This would be consistent with a philosophy of \"support the stop operation regardless of your state\".\n\nWithout that you can't reliably clean up during failed start operations -which the CompositeService itself tries to do by stopping all child services if any one of them fails to start - including the service that failed.",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=stevel%40apache.org",
          "name": "stevel@apache.org",
          "key": "stevel@apache.org",
          "avatarUrls": {
